column1: Comp sales curves below are per performance, single tickets only.  Sub, Capacity, OCC% are provided for reference, perhaps helpful to cite in the dashboard in tooltip or elsewhere?

We have the comps at daily grain (Fri,Sat,Sun) but for now simplifying to use averages as same comp for every performance day (unless Piazza).  We may go to day-level comps in the future but need to learn more.

Important note: in our current methodology, we project to week of ("0") but not all the way through Final (Mon after performance).  We need to start doing that going forward, which is a change, so "Final" is a new column.
We have not yet incorporated performance tiers into our comp methodology but may in the future.
Use "Comp Desc" as the label for the target line in the dashboard

Where "Piazza Default" or "Global Default" are listed for "Comp Desc", use those target lines.  24-25 Piazzas were CS3,4,6,8,9,10,14.  Both of these are imperfect but better than the 4-year averages that are the current defaults
Pops Sundays always have low subs, so they have different comps
We have IDed comps but are missing some of the 10-week sales data for comps further out and will fill this in over time

column4: # weeks out ("0" is Monday of performance week, "Final" is Monday following performance)
